Constructor Detail

Note

public Note(char baseNote,
            int octaveModifier,
            Accidental accidentalModifier,
            double noteMultiplier)
Creates a Note object

Parameters:
baseNote - char representing the base note
octaveModifier - integer represnting the number of octaves up or down from the base note. Passed value of 0 means no octave modification.
accidentalModifier - Accidental object representing the accidental applied to this Note. A passed value of null corresponds to no accidental.
noteMultiplier - double modifier of the note length. A passed value of 1 indicates that note length is equal to the default note length specified in the Header associated with the Player object that this Note belongs to.
Throws:
java.lang.RuntimeException - in case of invalid baseNote
